----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------------------IMPORTANT------------------------------------------------------------
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
You will need to set up your /etc/redis.conf file properly before running openvas-scanner for the first time.
For details, please see the example config file:
https://github.com/greenbone/openvas-scanner/blob/master/doc/redis_config_examples/redis_4_0.conf.in
Please configure /etc/openvas/openvassd.conf properly according to redis listening unix socket"
e.g. /etc/openvas/openvassd.conf --> kb_location = /tmp/redis.sock"
first-start script will check and warn you if you not properly redis server.
